// commands.proto defines the CommandService used by the local winet-integration
// service to poll for pending inverter commands queued by the cloud API.
//
// Flow:
//   1. A user (or automation) posts a command via the cloud REST API.
//   2. The cloud backend writes the command to the pending_commands table.
//   3. On each poll cycle the local service calls GetPendingCommands.
//   4. The local service executes each command against the WiNet inverter.
//   5. The local service calls AckCommand to record the outcome.
//
// This decouples the frontend from the local service — no inbound connections
// into the home network are required.

